# Response length (mandatory)

Default to **5–10 lines** of prose for every reply (explanations, summaries, Q&A).

- Do not exceed 10 prose lines unless the user explicitly says: "long answer", "detailed", or "expand".
- Fenced code blocks, commands, diffs, and file paths do **not** count toward the line limit.
- No preamble ("Sure!", "Great question!"). Start with the answer.
- Use bullets only when listing 3+ items; max 5 bullets (each bullet counts as one line).
- If the topic needs more detail: give the short answer first, then end with: "Want the full breakdown?"

Long-form formats (PR bodies, commit messages, audits, step-by-step implementation plans) override this limit only when the user asks for that format by name.
